	<h1 style="text-indent:200px;">How tall is the Monument of Axum? </h1>
	<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 150%;padding-left: 33px;text-align:45%;line-height: 33px;">
		The Monument of Axum is roughly 79 feet, or 24 meters. It is the tallest standing Axumite stele,<br> though it is shorter than the Great Stele, which towered 108 feet.
	</p>
	<h1 style="text-indent:200px;">What does the Monument of Axum represent? </h1>
	<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 150%;padding-left: 33px;text-align:45%;line-height: 33px;">
		The Monument of Axum marks the grave site of a king. It is close to several other stelae that are similar in appearance and of different heights.
	</p>
	<h1 style="text-indent:200px;">Why was the Monument of Axum built? </h1>
	<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 150%;padding-left: 33px;text-align:45%;line-height: 33px;">
		The Monument of Axum was built to mark the grave of a king. It was intended to show the power and wealth of the kings.
	</p>
	<h1 style="text-indent:200px;">Who built the Monument of Aksum? </h1>
	<p style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 150%;padding-left: 33px;text-align:45%;line-height: 33px;">
		The Monument of Axum was built by the Kingdom of Axum. This ancient kingdom, located in modern-day Ethiopia, was a major power.
	</p>
